content:
RSIN was founded in 2003 and is headquartered in Fuzhou, Fujian Province . we mainly conduct business in Nigeria and other western African countries. over the past 20 years of development, we have become a multinational corporation with diversified industrial clusters of iron and steel, textile, fiber chemical and lead-acid battery manufacturing based on the construction of circular economy industrial park

We are recruiting to fill the position below:

Job Position: Recruitment Manager
Job Location: Abeokuta, Ogun
Employment Type: Full-time

Job Responsibilities








	Responsible for the selection, training and retention of Nigerian team members in the region in charge;
	Responsible for recruiting high-end Nigerian talents in the region in charge;
	Responsible for background investigation of high-level Nigerian personnel in the region;
	Responsible for the induction training, corporate culture training and capacity building training of Nigerian employees in the region in charge;
	Responsible for the promotion of the company's headquarters policies and systems and the supervision and implementation of the systems;
	Responsible for connecting with the company's headquarters for personnel-related work;
	Responsible for assisting Chinese managers in the region to carry out corporate cultural activities and seminars;


Qualifications


	University degree preferred;
	More than 3 years of experience in human resources management and recruitment;
	University major in human resources management and business management is preferred;
	Able to operate computers and use office software, with strong team management, organization, coordination and communication skills;
	Candidates with Chinese communication skills are preferred (preferably with Chinese communication skills);
	Priority is given to those working in Chinese or foreign companies.


Salary
N150,000 - N250,000 per month.

Method of Application
Interested and qualified candidates should send their CV to: stellarinternationalhr@gmail.com using the Job Position as the subject of the mail.    



